  "Iliacus branch of iliolumbar artery.r": {
    "id": "Iliacus branch of iliolumbar artery.r",
    "system": "Cardiovascular",
    "group": "Body (Abdomen & Pelvis)",
    "name": "Iliacus branch of iliolumbar artery",
    "side": "Right",
    "description": "\n\nILIOLUMBAR ARTERY\n\n\nThe iliac branch of the iliolumbar artery (ramus iliacus) descends to supply the iliacus muscle; some offsets, running between the muscle and the bone, anastomose with the iliac branches of the obturator artery; one of these enters an oblique canal to supply the bone, while others run along the crest of the ilium, distributing branches to the gluteal and abdominal muscles, and anastomosing in their course with the superior gluteal artery, iliac circumflex artery, and the lateral circumflex femoral artery. \n\nThis anastamosis occurs around the anterior superior iliac spine. \n\n\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iliac_branch_of_iliolumbar_artery",
    "function": "Carries blood to facilitate gas, nutrient, and waste exchange across the tissue beds.",
    "clinical": "Involved in peripheral vascular diseases, thromboses, or aneurysms."
  },
  "Lumbar branch of iliolumbar artery.r": {
    "id": "Lumbar branch of iliolumbar artery.r",
    "system": "Cardiovascular",
    "group": "Body (Abdomen & Pelvis)",
    "name": "Lumbar branch of iliolumbar artery",
    "side": "Right",
    "description": "\n\nLUMBAR BRANCH OF ILIOLUMBAR ARTERY\n\n\nThe lumbar branch of the iliolumbar artery (ramus lumbalis) supplies the psoas major and quadratus lumborum, anastomoses with the last lumbar artery, and sends a small spinal branch through the intervertebral foramen between the last lumbar vertebra and the sacrum, into the vertebral canal to supply the cauda equina.\n\n\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lumbar_branch_of_iliolumbar_artery",
    "function": "Carries blood to facilitate gas, nutrient, and waste exchange across the tissue beds.",
    "clinical": "Involved in peripheral vascular diseases, thromboses, or aneurysms."
  },
