  "Plantar metatarsal veins.l": {
    "id": "Plantar metatarsal veins.l",
    "system": "Cardiovascular",
    "group": "Lower Limbs (Legs/Feet)",
    "name": "Plantar metatarsal veins",
    "side": "Left",
    "description": "\n\nPLANTAR METATARSAL VEINS\n\n\nThe plantar metatarsal veins run backward in the metatarsal spaces, collect blood from digital veins and communicate, by means of perforating veins, with the veins on the dorsum of the foot, and unite to form the deep plantar venous arch which lies alongside the plantar arterial arch.\n\n\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plantar_metatarsal_veins",
    "function": "Carries blood to facilitate gas, nutrient, and waste exchange across the tissue beds.",
    "clinical": "Involved in peripheral vascular diseases, thromboses, or aneurysms."
  },
  "Plantar venous arch.l": {
    "id": "Plantar venous arch.l",
    "system": "Cardiovascular",
    "group": "Lower Limbs (Legs/Feet)",
    "name": "Plantar venous arch",
    "side": "Left",
    "description": "\n\nPLANTAR VENOUS ARCH\n\n\nThe four plantar metatarsal veins run backward in the metatarsal spaces, communicate, by means of perforating veins, with the veins on the dorsum of the foot, and unite to form the plantar venous arch (or deep plantar venous arch) which lies alongside the plantar arterial arch.\nFrom the deep plantar venous arch the medial and lateral plantar veins run backward close to the corresponding arteries and, after communicating with the great and small saphenous veins, unite behind the medial malleolus to form the posterior tibial veins.\n\n\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plantar_venous_arch",
    "function": "Carries blood to facilitate gas, nutrient, and waste exchange across the tissue beds.",
    "clinical": "Involved in peripheral vascular diseases, thromboses, or aneurysms."
  },
