    "name": "Inferior labial veins",
    "side": "Left",
    "description": "\n\nINFERIOR LABIAL VEINS\n\n\nThe inferior labial veins drain the blood of the inferior part of the oral region to the facial vein, then to the common facial vein, then to the internal jugular vein.\n\n",
